<div><div><h2>-</h2></div><div>an anti-corruption court has indicted former pakistan prime minister nawaz sharif his daughter and son-in-law in the latest development set off by <a href="https://panamapapers.icij.org/the_power_players/ lang=en& autoresize=true#19">disclosures in the panama papers</a>. the panama papers revealed the the family used offshore companies to buy expensive london properties. sharif resigned in july after <a href="https://panamapapers.icij.org/20170728-pakistan-pm-disqualified.html">pakistan\xe2\x80\x99s supreme court ruled he was disqualified</a> to hold the country\xe2\x80\x99s highest office for having assets \xe2\x80\x9cdisproportionate to his known means of income.\xe2\x80\x9d sharif did not attend the oct. 18 hearing. he was in london where his wife is undergoing surgery and sent a plea of not guilty. his daughter maryam sharif and his son mohammad safdar pleaded not guilty at the hearing. \xe2\x80\x94 maryam nawaz sharif (@maryamnsharif) <a href="https://twitter.com/maryamnsharif/status/917736110289313792 ref_src=twsrc%5etfw">october 10 2017</a> <script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script> sharif labelled the proceedings a \xe2\x80\x9cmurder of justice\xe2\x80\x9d when speaking to <a href="https://www.geo.tv/latest/163545-nawaz-terms-nab-proceedings-as-murder-of-justice">reporters in london</a> after the announcement. \xe2\x80\x9cyou tell me if this is justice or murder of justice\xe2\x80\x9d he asked reporters.<br />he said he would not accept the decision because it did not expose any \xe2\x80\x9ccorruption or government kickbacks\xe2\x80\x9d.<br />also speaking afterwards maryam sharif who had been seen as her father\xe2\x80\x99s eventual successor said the family would fight the charges. \xe2\x80\x9ci refuse to accept the charges\xe2\x80\x9d she said outside the courthouse. \xe2\x80\x9cwe are being denied a fundamental right to justice.\xe2\x80\x9d sharif\xe2\x80\x99s supporters have blamed his troubles on the military which ousted him in 1999. and despite his continuing legal problems the pakistan muslim league-nawaz (pml-n) re-elected him as its leader earlier this month. the indictment was triggered by a national accountability bureau report on three cases of corruption and money laundering that involved sharif his family members and finance minister ishaq dar. the panama papers had reported that three of sharif\xe2\x80\x99s children were owners or had the right to authorize transactions for several companies including two that owned \xe2\x80\x9ca uk property each for use by the family\xe2\x80\x9d of the companies\xe2\x80\x99 owners. sharif\xe2\x80\x99s daughter mariam safdar was the owner of the two british virgin islands-based firms. according to the guardian newspaper hours before the indictment a <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/oct/19/ousted-pakistan-pm-nawaz-sharif-indicted-over-financial-allegations">delegation from the accountability bureau</a> arrived in london to collect evidence of the property owned by the sharif family. the bureau has asked the pakistani interior ministry to request interpol to issue red warrants for sharif\xe2\x80\x99s sons hussain and hassan in order for them to be extradited from the uk. the interior minister ahsan iqbal a close associate of sharif has yet to comply.</div></div>